From: piper firmware build <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] configure: do not use $TARGET env as multi-builddir name

libffi's configure (via the AX_ENABLE_BUILDDIR autoconf-archive macro)
auto-detects "multi-builddir" mode and reads $TARGET from the environment
as the subdirectory name, falling back to $target (the autoconf target
tuple) only if $TARGET is unset.

Buildroot's OpenIPC Makefile uses TARGET as a make variable
(TARGET=/b/output) and GNU Make exports command-line variables to recipe
subshells, so libffi configure sees TARGET=/b/output (an absolute path)
and tries to mkdir/cd into it then re-exec configure with broken
relative-path math, which fails with:

    /bin/bash: ../../.././configure: No such file or directory

This patch hits BOTH the generated configure script AND the m4 source
that AX_ENABLE_BUILDDIR expands from. Buildroot's libffi package runs
autoreconf, which regenerates configure from configure.ac + m4/, so
patching only configure gets wiped — hence the dual hunk. The m4 patch
is the canonical fix; the configure patch is a safety net in case
autoreconf is skipped.

Upstream: not submitted (libffi 3.4.6 changed this code path; this patch
fixes 3.4.4 which is what buildroot 2024.02 ships).

--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -3381,7 +3381,7 @@ if test ".$ac_srcdir_defaulted" != ".no" ; then
   else
     test ".$ax_enable_builddir" = "."  && ax_enable_builddir="."
     test ".$ax_enable_builddir" = ".no"  && ax_enable_builddir="."
-    test ".$TARGET" = "." && TARGET="$target"
+    TARGET="$target"
     test ".$ax_enable_builddir" = ".auto" && ax_enable_builddir="$TARGET"
     if test ".$ax_enable_builddir" != ".." ; then    # we know where to go and
       as_dir=$ax_enable_builddir; as_fn_mkdir_p
--- a/m4/ax_enable_builddir.m4
+++ b/m4/ax_enable_builddir.m4
@@ -101,7 +101,7 @@ AC_DEFUN([AX_ENABLE_BUILDDIR],[
   else
     test ".$SUB" = "."  && SUB="."
     test ".$SUB" = ".no"  && SUB="."
-    test ".$TARGET" = "." && TARGET="$target"
+    TARGET="$target"
     test ".$SUB" = ".auto" && SUB="m4_ifval([$1], [$1],[$TARGET])"
     if test ".$SUB" != ".." ; then    # we know where to go and
       AS_MKDIR_P([$SUB])
